                                    6960                     Ÿ    PARM LIST DEFINITIONS                                        Ÿ
                                    6961                     Ÿ                                                                 Ÿ
                                    6962                     Ÿ    NLIST - PARAMETER NAME LIST (AS DEFINED ON PROC STATEMENT)   Ÿ
                                    6963                     Ÿ    VLIST - PARAMETER VALUE LIST                                 Ÿ
                                    6964                     Ÿ  PLIST - PARAMETER NAME LIST (AS SPECIFIED ON PCALL STATEMENT)  Ÿ
                                    6965                     Ÿ                                                                 Ÿ
                                    6966                     Ÿ    NOTE: THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN A NLIST AND A PLIST (IN THIS    Ÿ
                                    6967                     Ÿ    PROGRAM) IS AS FOLLOWS:  A NLIST IS A LIST OF NAMES          Ÿ
                                    6968                     Ÿ    SPECIFIED ON A PROCEDURE DEFINITION,, THE NAMES MUST         Ÿ
                                    6969                     Ÿ    SIMPLE VARIABLE NAMES.  THESE VARIABLES WILL BECOME          Ÿ
                                    6970                     Ÿ    LOCAL VARIABLES OF THE PROCEDURE.  A PLIST IS A LIST         Ÿ
                                    6971                     Ÿ    OF PARM VARIABLE NAMES THAT ARE PASSED TO A PROCEDURE,, AS   Ÿ
                                    6972                     Ÿ    SOME OF THE PARAMETERS MAY BE EXPRESSIONS OR CONSTANTS       Ÿ
                                    6973                     Ÿ    NOT ALL THE ENTRIES IN A PLIST EXIST,, ONLY VARIABLE         Ÿ
                                    6974                     Ÿ    NAME ENTRIES EXIST,,, CONSTANT OR EXPRESSION ENTRIES ARE     Ÿ
                                    6975                     Ÿ    ZERO.                                                        Ÿ

1FLOW     (FLOW2025) (12:45) (15MAR04) EXEC Formatting Routines                                                             Page   64
0Current Usings:  (CP,R11) (CV,R12)
0Loc    Object Code    Addr1 Addr2  Stmt Lv Lineno    Source Statement           (Hibal 5, Asmedit 3.3)  HLASM R4.0  2004/03/15 12.45

0                                  15972              ¿þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþÜ
                                   15973              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   15974              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   15975              Ÿ  FFORMAT - FORMAT XPROC                                             Ÿ
                                   15976              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   15977              Ÿ  ON ENTRY:                                                          Ÿ
                                   15978              Ÿ       R0 - OPTIONS                                                  Ÿ
                                   15979              Ÿ             C'    ' - DEFAULT FORMATTING                            Ÿ
                                   15980              Ÿ             C'M   ' - MARK ACTIVE, FORMATED (DEFAULT FOR MARK)      Ÿ
                                   15981              Ÿ             C'MU  ' - MARK ACTIVE, UNFORMATED                       Ÿ
                                   15982              Ÿ       R1 - INDENT VALUE                                             Ÿ
                                   15983              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   15984              Ÿ  ON EXIT:                                                           Ÿ
                                   15985              Ÿ       R15 - CC=ZERO,  ALL ERRORS EXIT VIA CVERROR                   Ÿ
                                   15986              Ÿ       ACTIVE FILE FORMATED  AND/OR  MARKED.                         Ÿ
                                   15987              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   15988              Ÿ  NOTES:                                                             Ÿ
                                   15989              Ÿ    FILE MUST BE XSCANNED PRIOR TO CALLING THIS ROUTINE.             Ÿ
                                   15990              Ÿ    THIS ACCOMPLISHES THE FOLLOWING:                                 Ÿ
                                   15991              Ÿ       1. SYNTAX IS ALREADY SCANNED AND OK                           Ÿ
                                   15992              Ÿ       2. CONTINUATATION LINES ARE CONCATENATED                      Ÿ
                                   15993              Ÿ       3. SCANNED FILE IS IN TEMP EXEC FILE                          Ÿ
                                   15994              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   15995              Ÿ    WE NOTE THAT THE TEMP EXEC FILE IS DIFFERENT THAN THE            Ÿ
                                   15996              Ÿ    ACTIVE FILE IN THE FOLLOWING RESPECTS:                           Ÿ
                                   15997              Ÿ       1. CONTINUATION LINES ARE CONCATENATED.                       Ÿ
                                   15998              Ÿ       2. COMMENT LINES ARE DELETED                                  Ÿ
                                   15999              Ÿ       3. BLANK (NULL) LINES ARE DELETED                             Ÿ
                                   16000              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   16001              Ÿ    THE STRATEGY IS:                                                 Ÿ
                                   16002              Ÿ    WE SCAN THE TEMP EXEC FILE FOR BEGIN/END NESTING.                Ÿ
                                   16003              Ÿ    THIS NESTING DETERMINES THE ACTIVE FILE INDENTING..              Ÿ
                                   16004              Ÿ    WE READ FROM THE ACTIVE AND REWRITE TO THE ACTIVE                Ÿ
                                   16005              Ÿ    PROPERLY INDENTED LINES.   LINES THAT EXIST IN THE               Ÿ
                                   16006              Ÿ    ACTIVE FILE BUT ARE NOT IN THE TEMP LOADED EXEC                  Ÿ
                                   16007              Ÿ    ARE CONTINUATION LINES, UNLESS THEY ARE COMMENT                  Ÿ
                                   16008              Ÿ    LINES OR BLANK LINES.                                            Ÿ
                                   16009              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   16010              Ÿ    NOTE:  IT MAY BE BEST AT SOME POINT TO RECODE THIS               Ÿ
                                   16011              Ÿ    ROUTINE TO SCAN FOR BEGIN/END, CONTINUATIONS, ETC. ETC.          Ÿ
                                   16012              Ÿ    DIRECTLY FROM THE ACTIVE FILE.  IF YOU GOT THE TIME,,,           Ÿ
                                   16013              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   16014              Ÿ  *** CAUTION ***                                                    Ÿ
                                   16015              Ÿ  CAUTION:  ACTIVE FILE MUST BE XSCANNED (INSURES SYNTACTICAL        Ÿ
                                   16016              Ÿ    VALIDITY) BEFORE CALLING FFORMAT.   IE. TEMP LOAD FILE           Ÿ
                                   16017              Ÿ    MUST CONTAIN XSCANNED ACTIVE FILE.                               Ÿ
                                   16018              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   16019              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                                      ¾þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþ»

                                   22512              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   22513              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   22514              Ÿ  FCIF -  IF FLOW PROCESSING                                         Ÿ
                                   22515              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   22516              Ÿ  ON ENTRY:                                                          Ÿ
                                   22517              Ÿ      @R1 - LINE AREA                                                Ÿ
                                   22518              Ÿ      @R2 - LINE NUMBER (OF IF STATEMENT)                            Ÿ
                                   22519              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   22520              Ÿ  ON EXIT:                                                           Ÿ
                                   22521              Ÿ      @R2 - LINE NUMBER (OF END OF IF STRUCTURE)                     Ÿ
                                   22522              Ÿ      R15 - CC=ZERO                                                  Ÿ
                                   22523              Ÿ            ERRORS EXIT VIA FCERR, THEN CVERROR                      Ÿ
                                   22524              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   22525              Ÿ  IF FLOW PROCESSING IS A BIT COMPLICATED BY TWO UNUSUAL             Ÿ
                                   22526              Ÿ  CONDITIONS.  FIRST, AN IF DOES NOT REQUIRE A BEGIN-END BLOCK.      Ÿ
                                   22527              Ÿ  THAT IS AN IF MAY BE FOLLOWED DIRECTLY BY A SINGLE STATEMENT.      Ÿ
                                   22528              Ÿ  THIS IS ALLOWED FOR CONVENIENCE REASONS.  SECOND, AN IF BLOCK      Ÿ
                                   22529              Ÿ  MAY BE FOLLOWED BY AN 'ELSE' OR 'ELSEIF' BLOCK.  DIG IT.           Ÿ
                                   22530              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   22531              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                                      ¾þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþ»

                                   23409              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   23410              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   23411              Ÿ  FCELSEIF -  ELSEIF FLOW PROCESSING                                 Ÿ
                                   23412              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   23413              Ÿ  ON ENTRY:                                                          Ÿ
                                   23414              Ÿ      @R1 - LINE AREA                                                Ÿ
                                   23415              Ÿ      @R2 - LINE NUMBER (OF ELSEIF STATEMENT)                        Ÿ
                                   23416              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   23417              Ÿ  ON EXIT:                                                           Ÿ
                                   23418              Ÿ      @R2 - LINE NUMBER (OF END OF ELSEIF STRUCTURE)                 Ÿ
                                   23419              Ÿ      R15 - CC=ZERO                                                  Ÿ
                                   23420              Ÿ            ERRORS EXIT VIA FCERR, THEN CVERROR                      Ÿ
                                   23421              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   23422              Ÿ  THIS ROUTINE IS VERY SIMILAR TO THE 'IF' FLOW CONTROL ROUTINE.     Ÿ
                                   23423              Ÿ  IT IS (AS IS THE 'IF' ROUTINE) COMPLICATED BY TWO UNUSUAL          Ÿ
                                   23424              Ÿ  CONDITIONS.  FIRST, AN ELSEIF DOES NOT REQUIRE A BEGIN-END BLOCK.  Ÿ
                                   23425              Ÿ  THAT IS AN ELSEIF MAY BE FOLLOWED DIRECTLY BY A SINGLE STATEMENT.  Ÿ
                                   23426              Ÿ  THIS IS ALLOWED FOR CONVENIENCE REASONS.  SECOND, AN ELSEIF        Ÿ
                                   23427              Ÿ  BLOCK MAY BE FOLLOWED BY AN 'ELSE' OR 'ELSEIF' BLOCK. DIG IT.      Ÿ
                                   23428              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   23429              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                                      ¾þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþ»

                                   25667              Ÿ  COMMENTS: THIS ROUTINE IS THE HEART OF THE FLOW CONTROL SCAN       Ÿ
                                   25668              Ÿ  ROUTINES.  IT IS CALLED RECURSIVELY.  AS THIS ROUTINE SCANS        Ÿ
                                   25669              Ÿ  FOR ITS MATCHING END,, IT WILL BRANCH OFF TO PROCESS ANY FLOW      Ÿ
                                   25670              Ÿ  CONTROL STATEMENTS IT ENCOUNTERS.  (EG. IF, WHILE, DO ...)         Ÿ
                                   25671              Ÿ  EACH OF THESE ROUTINES IN TURN WILL CALL THIS ROUTINE TO FIND      Ÿ
                                   25672              Ÿ  THEIR MATCHING END.  DIG IT !                                      Ÿ
                                   25673              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   25674              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                                      ¾þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþ»

                                   27824              Ÿ       R1 - LOCATION OF TEXT, (AT OR BEFORE '(')                     Ÿ

                                   27826              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   27827              Ÿ  ON EXIT:                                                           Ÿ

                                   27830              Ÿ      R15 - CC=ZERO, EXPRESSION SKIPPED OK                           Ÿ

                                   27834              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ

                                   31930              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   31931              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   31932              Ÿ  CHKDEF - CHECK IF DEFINED                                          Ÿ
                                   31933              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   31934              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   31935              Ÿ  ON ENTRY:                                                          Ÿ
                                   31936              Ÿ      @R1 - NAME OF LABEL/PROCEDURE                                  Ÿ
                                   31937              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   31938              Ÿ  ON EXIT:                                                           Ÿ
                                   31939              Ÿ      R15 - CC=ZERO, DEFINED                                         Ÿ
                                   31940              Ÿ            CC=NZ, NOT DEFINED                                       Ÿ
                                   31941              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   31942              Ÿ  NOTE: ROUTINE CALLS GETFINFO TO TRY TO GET A PREVIOUS ENTRY.       Ÿ
                                   31943              Ÿ        THE PARMS FOR GETFINFO ARE A BIT WILD AND WOOLLY             Ÿ
                                   31944              Ÿ        THE GETFLOW ROUTINE CANNOT BE USED HERE BECAUSE IT           Ÿ
                                   31945              Ÿ        READS FROM THE EXECUTING EXEC FILE NOT THE LOADING           Ÿ
                                   31946              Ÿ        EXEC FILE.                                                   Ÿ
                                   31947              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   31948              Ÿ  CAUTION: THIS ROUTINE IS USED FOR CHECKING TO SEE IF A NAME        Ÿ
                                   31949              Ÿ        IS PREVIOUSLY DEFINED.  THIS ROUTINE SHOULD BE USED          Ÿ
                                   31950              Ÿ        EXCLUSIVELY DURING FLOW CONTROL PROCESSING AS IT CHECKS      Ÿ
                                   31951              Ÿ        THE FLOW CONTROL INFO FOR THE EXEC BEING LOADED AND NOT      Ÿ
                                   31952              Ÿ        THE EXEC THAT IS BEING EXECUTED.                             Ÿ
